	"description": "We can add a drop shadow to any HTML element using the CSS property box-shadow.\nHere&#x27;s how.\n\nAdding a Basic Drop Shadow\nLet&#x27;s first set up some basic HTML elements to add our drop shadows to:\n\n&lt;div id&#x3D;&quot;box1&quot; class&#x3D;&quot;box&quot;&gt;Box1&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div id&#x3D;&quot;box2&quot; class&#x3D;&quot;box&quot;&gt;Box2&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div id&#x3D;&quot;box3&quot; class&#x3D;&quot;box&quot;&gt;Box3&lt;/div&gt;\n\nThen add some basic CSS:\n\np {\n    padding: 10px;\n}\n.box {\n    padding: 20px;\n    width: 50%;\n    margin: 30px auto;\n    background: #000;\n    color: #fff;\n}\n\nThe result is just three black box",
